The paper deals with privacy-preserving query systems for mobile users, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel approach to location cloaking on road networks using the concept of stars and cloaking graphs, which involves graph theory and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses cost-aware star selection decisions, which involves optimization and decision-making (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with location-based queries, which is a topic that falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and spatial information systems (cs.SI).
